list.abstract: List，属于计算机专业术语，是编程语言中类库中的一个类，可以简单视之为双向连结串行，以线性列的方式管理物件集合。list的特点是可以快速在集合的任何位置增加或删除元素，但不支持随机存取。list以模板方式实现（即泛型），可以处理任意型别的变量，包括使用者自定义的资料型态。 List是类库提供的众多容器（container）之一，除List之外还有vector、set、map等。
list是一个英语单词，名词、动词，作名词时意思是“列表，清单，目录；（船的）倾斜”，作动词时意思是“列清单；把…列入一览表；被列入价目表；把…列入正式名单（尤指医院或法庭的名单）；（船只）倾斜； 使(公司) 上市”。

yingyinNormal.en: This is an impressive list of hobbies.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的兴趣爱好可真厉害。

yingyinNormal.en: What's next on the list, Peppa? Crisps!
yingyinNormal.zh: 清单上的下一项是什么，佩佩？薯片！

yingyinNormal.en: Aamir Barkawi. Number 6 on the 10 list.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哈密尔·巴卡维。十人名单中的第六个。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm confused, because there's not a list?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我糊涂了，完全没有清单？
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: A signal box, that's on our list, Hooray!
yingyinNormal.zh: 信号盒。我们的清单上面有这个！噢耶！

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I would never leave you off my list.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我决不会把你从我的名单除名。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a short list. Great. I like it. Focus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那清单非常短。很好，我喜欢，讲重点。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: That just puts us higher on their kill list.
yingyinNormal.zh: 跟他们同盟也许会更危险。

yingyinNormal.en: I can see clouds. Are clouds on the list? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我看到了白云。可白云在表格上吗？不在。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay! First thing on my list, get registered.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第一项任务，注册。

yingyinNormal.en: Chocolate cake? Chocolate cake? Is that on the list?
yingyinNormal.zh: 巧克力蛋糕？在清单上吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You memorized conjugations for an endless list of verbs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 背了无数个动词变化。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. We're very popular. There's a two-year waiting list. Sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，这里很受欢迎，预约已经排到2年后，抱歉。

yingyinNormal.en: That's nearly everything on our list. There's one last thing on the list. A plant? Is that on the list?
yingyinNormal.zh: 清单上的东西几乎都有了。清单上还有一种东西。一棵植物？清单上有吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Very good. That's nearly everything on our list. There's one last thing on the list. A plant? Is that on the list?
yingyinNormal.zh: 非常好，清单上的东西几乎都有了。清单上还有一种东西。一棵植物？清单上有吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You wanna be on my list too? Keep talking. Has anyone seem my list by the way?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你想榜上有名就继续说啊，对了，谁有看到我的黑名单？

yingyinNormal.en: Is Granddad dog on the list? Silly Peppa, my Granddad won't be on the list. But he is sailing a boat. And a boat is on the list.
yingyinNormal.zh: 狗爷爷在活动表格上吗？糊涂的佩奇，我的爷爷怎么会在表格上呢。但是他开的一艘船。而一艘船在表格上。

yingyinNormal.en: Go back to the list? He was fine, but I'm not enthused by anyone else on that list.
yingyinNormal.zh: 再看看名单？他还好，但那张名单上别人我都没兴趣。

yingyinNormal.en: Is Granddad dog on the list? Silly Peppa, my granddad won't be on the list. But he is sailing a boat. And a boat is on the list. Hooray!
yingyinNormal.zh: 单子上有狗爷爷吗？笨佩佩，我的狗爷爷不会在清单上的。可是他在划船。而清单上面有船。噢耶！

yingyinNormal.en: A plant? Is that on the list? Oh, no, George. The last thing on the list is fruit. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个植物？在清单上吗？噢，不，乔治。清单上最后一项是水果。噢。

examination_example.sentence: A fifth grader gets a homework assignment to select his future career path from a <highlight>list</highlight> of occupations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 五年级学生得到一份家庭作业，要从职业列表中选择他未来的职业道路。

examination_example.sentence: Harford argues that inevitable distractions often render the daily to-do <highlight>list</highlight> ineffective, while leaving room for improvisation in such a <highlight>list</highlight> can reap the best results.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 哈福德认为，不可避免的干扰往往会使日常待办事项列表失效，而在这样的列表中留出即兴发挥的空间可以获得最佳结果。

examination_example.sentence: Another approach to getting more done in less time is to rethink how you prioritise your day — in particular how we craft our to-do <highlight>lists</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在更少的时间内完成更多工作的另一种方法是重新考虑如何安排你一天的工作，尤其是如何列出待办清单。

examination_example.sentence: Many students find themselves <highlight>listing</highlight> one major on their college applications, but switching to another after taking college classes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多学生发现自己在大学申请表上列出了一个专业，但在上完大学课程后又转到了另一个专业。

examination_example.sentence: The crash was a major reason the U. S. Fish and Wildlife Service (USFWS) decided to formally <highlight>list</highlight> the bird as threatened.
examination_example.sentence_trans: （小草原松鸡）数量的锐减是促使美国鱼类及野生动植物管理局决定正式将其列入“受到威胁”物种的主要原因。

examination_example.sentence: The major reason for <highlight>listing</highlight> the lesser prairie chicken as threatened is its drastically decreased population
examination_example.sentence_trans: 将小松鸡列为濒危物种的主要原因是它数量的急剧减少。
